definitions.definition: A hypothetical extinct Indo-European language , supposed to have been spoken distinct from Celtic in late prehistory , in certain parts of what has become known as Gaul .

main_definition: ( linguistics ) A hypothetical extinct Indo-European language , supposed to have been spoken distinct from Celtic in late prehistory , in certain parts of what has become known as Gaul .
